headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 17 of his 23 points in the third quarter, Kentavious Caldwell-Pope added 16, and Deni Avdija had 12 points and a career-high 15 rebounds as the Washington Wizards sent the Detroit Pistons to their eighth straight loss, 103-94 on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma scores 23, Wizards deal Pistons 8th straight loss

headlines.description: — In his first game as a member of the Nets, Seth Curry scored 23 points to lead Brooklyn to a 109-85 win over the Sacramento Kings on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry leads new-look Nets in 109-85 rout of Kings

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Josh Giddey and Tre Mann, Oklahoma City’s two first-round picks from the 2021 NBA Draft were looking forward to playing at Madison Square Garden. They certainly won’t forget the career nights they enjoyed.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giddey, Randle post triple-doubles; Thunder top Knicks in OT

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Taking a deeper look at quite possibly the best stretch of his career, DeMar DeRozan described a conversation he had with boxer Floyd Mayweather a few years ago.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan scores 40 as Bulls rally past Spurs 120-109

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons’ hot streak has helped the Portland Trail Blazers thrive after reshaping their roster at the trade deadline.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons scores 31, Portland beats Giannis-less Bucks 122-107

events.name: Toronto Raptors at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum's first victory with New Orleans was one of the Pelicans' most dominant performances of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum leads hot-shooting Pelicans past Raptors, 120-90

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 26 points to lead six Denver players in double figures, and the Nuggets beat the Orlando Magic 121-111. on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic nets 26, Denver's balanced scoring too much for Magic

headlines.description: — The Utah Jazz are starting to roll again and Rudy Gobert’s return makes them look that much better.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gobert back, Mitchell leads way for Jazz in win over Rockets

events.name: Golden State Warriors at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Terance Mann and the Los Angeles Clippers are beginning to prove they can consistently overcome big games by opposing superstars.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mann scores season-high 25, Clippers defeat Warriors 119-104
